# Source of Truth

The portfolio must be generated using the following files:

## Structure Definition
- File: /idea/structure.md
- Purpose:
  - Defines page layout
  - Defines section order
  - Defines UI/UX design ideas
  - Defines visual behavior (grid, hero, etc.)

## Content Source
- File: /idea/resume.md
- Purpose:
  - Provides ALL actual content
  - Includes skills, projects, experience, contact info

---

# Rules for Agent

## 1. Separation of Concerns
- NEVER invent content
- ALWAYS pull content from resume.md
- ALWAYS follow layout from structure.md

## 2. Mapping Logic
- Hero section → use name + summary from resume.md
- About section → use professional summary
- Skills section → map skills categories directly
- Projects section → map projects exactly
- Experience section → map work experience
- Contact section → map contact info

## 3. Consistency
- Ensure structure.md and resume.md stay synchronized
- If mismatch occurs:
  - prioritize structure.md for layout
  - prioritize resume.md for content

## 4. Output Expectations
- Generate clean React/Next.js components
- Use shadcn + Tailwind
- Apply motion.dev where appropriate


## 5. Restrictions
- Do NOT modify source files
- Do NOT duplicate content unnecessarily
- Do NOT create fake projects or skills
- Do NOT write scripts, parsers, or utilities to read these files programmatically
- Do NOT create data-fetching logic (e.g., file readers, loaders, APIs)
- Do NOT convert these files into runtime data sources
- Do NOT dynamically import or parse `.md` files in the application